                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Earl of Elgin</gloss> to Governor Sir
                            <persName type="to">W. MacGregor</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Downing Street</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-09-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 19.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of even date, please state whether your ministers, in
                    the event of the negotiations for a modus vivendi breaking down, are prepared to
                    indemnify His Majesty’s Government against any claims for compensation which may
                    be preferred by United States Government, and which it may not be possible
                    consistently with a fair interpretation of treaty rights to refuse; also
                    whether, in the event of a reference to arbitration becoming in the opinion of
                    His Majesty’s Government necessary or desirable, your ministers will agree to
                    such reference, and undertake to meet expenses of arbitration and pay the award,
                    if any.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
